wiki.content: Introducing "Jack In The Box" is the album’s lead single “ MORE” by BTS member, ​j-hope. The song marks his solo comeback since Hope World. On “MORE”, j-hope explores how he wants a successful life as a singer, although he knows money and fame aren’t everything that he needs. These themes are expressed through an addicting hip-hop and punk-rock rhythm. The song "MORE" by j-hope is all about the desire for personal growth, success, and achievement. The lyrics describe the rapper's determination to learn and improve through hard work and perseverance. In the first verse, he highlights his passion for music and the ongoing process of growth and learning. He acknowledges that the journey of learning is endless, and he is always striving to become better and more successful. The chorus of the song features the rapper shouting out for "more," emphasizing his desire to achieve more and go further in his art. The lyrics suggest that j-hope is ambitious and highly motivated, always pushing himself to surpass previous achievements and reach higher heights of success. The second verse of the song focuses on his work ethic, with a particular emphasis on the rapper's willingness to work tirelessly at his craft, always striving to improve, and never settling for mediocrity. In j-hope's view, true success is earned through hard work, dedication, and a willingness to push oneself beyond one's limits. Overall, the song "MORE" is an anthem of ambition and drive. It emphasizes the importance of staying focused on one's goals, working hard, and never settling for less than one's best. Through its lyrics, the song encourages listeners to embrace their passion, stay motivated, and keep striving for more. Read more on Last.fm.
